title: The Doobie Brothers -- Farewell Tour (extremely rare)
description:
I&#039;m taking a break from my normally scheduled Chicago upload to upload one of the greatest, if not the greatest, live albums ever.

The Doobies broke up in 1983.  Just as well, their name kept them in the 1970s.  But this album is without question the greatest live album ever.  Warner Brothers doesn&#039;t even market it any more, you have to go to Japan to get it (which I did -- thanks, EBay).  It cost be $75 but it&#039;s worth the cost.  You guys enjoy it for nothing.  And smoke some doobie.


This album contains:

Slippery St. Paul

Takin&#039; It to the Streets

Jesus Is Just Alright

Minute By Minute

Can&#039;t Let It Get Away

Echoes of Love

What a Fool Believes

Black Water

You Belong to Me

Slat Key Soquel Rag

Steamer Lane Breakdown

South City Midnight Lady

Olana

Don&#039;t Start Me Talkin&#039;

Long Train Runnin&#039;

China Grove


Enjoy!
